Answer: 
ðŸ—‚ï¸ Navigation Commands
| Command | Description             | Example                                            |
| ------- | ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `pwd`   | Print working directory | Shows your current directory â†’ `/home/salman`      |
| `ls`    | List files and folders  | `ls -l` â†’ detailed view (permissions, owner, date) |
| `cd`    | Change directory        | `cd Documents` â†’ go to Documents folder            |
| `cd ..` | Go one directory up     | From `/home/salman/Documents` â†’ `/home/salman`     |
| `clear` | Clear the terminal      | Removes previous outputs                           |

ðŸ“˜ Scenario:
Youâ€™re inside /home/salman/scripts but want to move to /home/salman/projects/security.

